metadata.name: Asemic Morphemes #19
metadata.description:
"Asemic Morphemes" is my second collection of asemic  writing. The first collection was “Asemic Writing 1o1”, which focused on letter placement and breaking the linear structures of writing.
In this collection, I have focused more on the structure of letters and morphemes.
According to the rules of this imaginary language, each morpheme consists of exactly three letters and the combination of all three letters together (48*48*48) creates 110,592 unique morphemes. The purpose of creating this collection is to challenge our understanding of the usual structures of human writing systems.

press ’s’ on the live mode to save the artwork.

Made with p5js.

metadata.name: ASSEMBLING MACHINE #239
metadata.description:
The machine never sleeps.
Build. Construct. Develop. Create. Form. Produce. Generate. Repeat.
---------------
Collectors at the highest tier (125 tez) may claim a signed 8”x10” print of their mint. Please look for details about prints on Twitter (@teaboswell), or contact me directly
---------------
CONTROLS:
A - Toggle loading animation (off by default to improve performance)
S - Download image
Double tap (mobile) - Download image
1-6 - Modify scale (1 = default, 2048 x 2730px, 6 = maximum, 12288 x 16380px (very performance intensive, will take a long time to render))
F - Fit to current screen size
G - Toggle grain overlay
L - Toggle background grid lines
B - Cycle border sizes (0 -> 100 -> 200 -> 300px)

You can modify the x and y url parameters to set a custom size. Note that the image will change to fit the new size, but overall drawing style, colors, etc. will remain the same.
(For example, for a 1000x2000 image, add &x=1000&y=2000)
---------------
teaboswell 2022

metadata.name: Bonsai Bonanza #585
metadata.description:
In previous works, I was attracted by the idea of ​​the domestication of plants.
According to Wikipedia, the purposes of bonsai are primarily contemplation for the viewer, and the pleasant exercise of effort and ingenuity for the grower. By contrast with other plant cultivation practices, bonsai is not intended for production of food or for medicine. Instead, bonsai practice focuses on long-term cultivation and shaping of one or more small trees growing in a container.
I pressume that the main intention is aesthetic. The beauty. Because we love beautiful things.
It is very interesting how we modify certain creatures for our sake of satisfaction.

May this collection brings you good fortune.

metadata.name: Uninhabitable #327
metadata.description:
Uninhabitable is a generative system built only from ellipses. The process of playing with different geometric and trigonometric disruptions gives rise to four different compositions which seek to evoque living constructions and environments. Besides the shape itself and its related distortion, the stroke weight of the lines plays a meaningful role in the piece. Following a discrete range [0.01,0.1,1] the weight reveals the process allowing the viewer to realize the trace of the huge amount of lines in each piece. This back and forth between scales and context is, while kind of stripping the code, part of my continuing interest on understanding the -usually- crazy paths of machines' way of thinking.

Press "h" to see it and high resolution and refresh to get back to the initial state. Press "h" to save it.

Uninhabitable is an original work by Iskra Velitchkova. 2021.

metadata.name: ylb-mess-A #189
metadata.description:
With colors and shapes reminiscent of childhood LEGO explorations, 'ylb-mess-A' explores the assembly process in reverse, using recursive subdivision to create detailed structures instead of progressively building a complex structure brick by brick. Although the tools I use to explore and create have changed over the years, this piece reminds me of the natural creative curiosity that was instilled in me at an early age, for which I am incredibly grateful.

metadata.name: Mount Doodle #233
metadata.description:
Tried my best to make every doodle aesthetically pleasing to the eyes.
However, just like nature, beauty often lies in imperfections. :)

Made with p5.js.
Primary split 5% with The Processing Foundation.

Keys
- 1: view 1000px png (Default)
- 2: download 2000px png
- 4: download 4000px png
- 8: download 8000px png
- s: save the image as PNG

When downloading higher resolution pngs, it might take several seconds to redraw the whole image. Download will start immediately after redrawing is completed. Please bear with the slow rendering.

metadata.name: Terra Nova #120
metadata.description:
In the year 2250, the first galactic sector stretching a few hundred parsecs were mapped and new worlds identified for the upcoming Terraforming missions. Who knows what one may stumble across wondering across the stars. Some of these planets feel at home, some feel off while the rest seem ALIVE. Part of the Terra universe

This piece consists of 6 layers driven by controlled noise to create different structures without the use of any external textures.

Keypress
‘Q’ Scroll across the environment
‘W’ Scroll across the minted color palette(1000 color variations)
‘E’  / ‘R’ / ‘T’ Toggle layer groups
‘Y’ To rotate the environment
‘O’ for performance details
‘P’ to pause environment rotation
‘S’ to take a high resolution 4096x4096 snapshot(in LIVE view only)
